<subSubSection id="C370650EFFC6FFD0FF1CF803BCA7C70E" box="[189,914,2030,2057]" pageId="21" pageNumber="242" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFC6FFD0FF1CF803BCA7C70E" blockId="21.[136,1452,1886,2093]" box="[189,914,2030,2057]" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FF1CF803BE7DC70E" bold="true" box="[189,328,2030,2056]" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Etymology:</emphasis>
—Named after host plant on which telia are formed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C370650EFFC6FFD3FF1CF7FFBA5DCE06" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="243" pageId="21" pageNumber="242" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFC6FFD3FF1CF7FFBA5DCE06" blockId="21.[136,1452,1886,2093]" lastBlockId="22.[136,1451,158,257]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="243" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FF1CF7FFBE64C72A" bold="true" box="[189,337,2066,2092]" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Description:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FECCF7FEBD37C72B" box="[365,514,2067,2093]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Spermogonia</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FDAFF7FEBD7EC72A" box="[526,587,2067,2092]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">aecia</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FDDAF7FFBDECC72A" box="[635,729,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">uredinia</emphasis>
not found. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FCF3F7FFBCBCC72A" box="[850,905,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Telia</emphasis>
hypophyllous, compact, blackish brown, rounded to broadly elliptic, erumpent. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC5FFD3FE76FF73BD63CFBE" box="[471,598,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="243">Teliospores</emphasis>
broadly clavate, ellipsoid, truncate and rounded at apices, constricted at the septa, attenuate at the bases, 38.0–53.5 × 17.5–22.5 µm (av. 40.5 × 17.5 µm); walls brown, 0.8–1.0 µm (av. 0.9 µm) thick at sides, 7.5–12.0 µm (av. 9.5 µm) at apices; pedicels persistent, hyaline, 9.0–16.0 µm (av. 12.5 µm) long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
